# Employee Management System

## Overview

The Employee Management System is a Python-based application developed using MySQL Database Connectivity to efficiently manage employee records. This project allows users to perform various employee management operations such as adding, updating, deleting, and viewing employee information through a user-friendly command-line interface.

The system is designed to simplify employee data management while demonstrating the practical implementation of Python programming, database connectivity, and CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

## Features

* Add new employee records
* View employee details
* Update employee information
* Delete employee records
* Search employees by ID
* Store employee data securely in a MySQL database
* Simple and interactive menu-driven interface

## Technologies Used

* Python
* MySQL
* MySQL Connector for Python

## Database Structure

### Database Name

`company_db`

### Table Name

`employees`

| Field Name     | Data Type         |
| -------------- | ----------------- |
| emp_id         | INT (Primary Key) |
| emp_name       | VARCHAR(100)      |
| emp_department | VARCHAR(100)      |
| emp_salary     | FLOAT             |
| emp_email      | VARCHAR(100)      |

## Learning Outcomes

This project helped in understanding:

* Python and MySQL integration
* Database connectivity using MySQL Connector
* SQL queries and database operations
* CRUD operations
* Exception handling
* Menu-driven application development

## Future Enhancements

* Graphical User Interface (GUI)
* Employee attendance management
* Payroll management system
* Authentication and user login
* Report generation and export functionality

## Conclusion

The Employee Management System is an effective solution for managing employee records while providing hands-on experience with Python programming and MySQL database management. It serves as an excellent beginner-to-intermediate level database project for students and aspiring software developers.
